  "prompt": "How can I change the \"Ok Google\" phrase to something else in a Nexus 6?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, the Android system doesn't support changing the \"Ok Google\" wake phrase to something else on the Nexus 6 or any other device. The phrase \"Ok Google\" is hardcoded into Google's voice recognition software and customizing it is not an available feature.\n\nGoogle Assistant's programming does not allow users to change the activation phrase because it is integral to its functionality and universally recognizable. Keeping a consistent wake phrase ensures the service can reliably detect when the user is attempting to make a request.\n\nHowever, you can use third-party applications that might offer similar functionality with customizable wake words. Be aware that these apps might not integrate as seamlessly with the Android system as Google Assistant does.\n\nIf you want to explore alternatives within the existing system, you might also consider setting up shortcuts or using certain smart home systems that might offer more flexibility in voice command customization, but the activation phrase for Google Assistant will remain \"Ok Google\" or \"Hey Google\".",
